<!-- EXCERPTS -->
<section class="excerpts">
<h2>The Waiting Rooms of My Life</h2>

<blockquote>
I have learned more about myself in waiting rooms than anywhere else in my life.
They are places where identity dissolves and survival quietly reshapes you.
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
Caregiving is not a moment of crisis.  
It is a long negotiation between love, endurance,
and systems never designed for you to survive them.
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
Time moves forward. Trauma does not.
The hallway changes. The fear remembers.
</blockquote>

</section>

